  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthened Protection From Gender-Based Violence in Adamawa State in North-East Nigeria &#x2013; Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prolonged conflict and complex humanitarian crisis in North-East Nigeria have led to one of the most protracted displacement situations in the region, exposing displaced populations to forms of gender-based violence (GBV) and sexual exploitation and abuse (SEA). To support survivors of GBV and other forms of abuse, IOM established a Multi-Purpose Community Hall (MPCH) in Malkhohi Local Government Area, Adamawa State in the first phase of this project, with the aim to create a safe space for the local communities to access a variety of services. With this second phase, IOM is working on the operationalization of the MPCH to be able to provide services to its users, including Mental Health and Psychosocial Support (MHPSS), case management, capacity building and skills training as well as sensitization activities.</narrative>
  </description>
